==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Totara
<hw>To"ta*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Maori.]</ety> <def>A
coniferous tree (<spn>Podocarpus totara</spn>), next to the kauri the
most valuable timber tree of New Zealand. Its hard reddish wood is used
for furniture and building, esp. in wharves, bridges, etc. Also
<altname>mahogany pine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tote</ent>⟦br⟧
